dave@tygra.Michigan.COM (David Conrad) writes:

> 1. I ftp'd RSAREF and extracted MD5 from it, and have compiled a program
> which calculates MD5 hashes of files.  Are there any restrictions on my
> use/distribution of this?

Nope, Rivest has put MD4 and MD5 into the public domain. There is some
requirement that if you are using them in your programs, you must
state that, the exact wording can be found in the comments at the
beginning of the C implementation.

> 2. Some time ago I ftp'd a document that described MD4 and contained
> source code implementing it, only my copy seems to be damaged, containing
> the description but only the first hundred lines or so of the reference
> implementation.  Does anyone have the whole thing? 

Try ftp.informatik.uni-hamburg.de:/pub/virus/texts/secutiry/md4.zip

> It is no longer on rsa.com.

It is now a RFC, I think, so it should be available at the sites that
carry such sort of stuff...

Regards,
Vesselin
